Node-js application environment setup.
Download the required files:-
Download the complete code from the OCI storage.
Please check the perquisite before downloading the node and oracle client.
https://yum.oracle.com/oracle-linux-nodejs.html
https://oracle.github.io/node-oracledb/doc/api.html#getstarted 
https://oracle.github.io/node-oracledb/INSTALL.html#instnoderpms
http://yum.oracle.com/repo/OracleLinux/OL7/oracle/instantclient/x86_64/index.html
Download node-js.
  
Download oracle instant-client.
 

1>>> Login to Server:-
 

2>>> Go to Sudo user ---- Command 
    		Sudo su –

3>>> yum update  -y
This command allows you to determine whether any updates are available for your installed packages. yum returns a list of all package updates from all repositories if any are available. This command is used to display information about advisories for packages that can be updated
If you have new server then it will take few minutes to update the package.
 
Completed 
 


4>>> create a directory 
mkdir <Any name>
Download the Code form Github 
Unzip the file 
5>>> Install node on the server  
rpm –i nodejs-12.16.1-1.e17.x86_64.rpm
Node version to check.
   	Node –v
	Npm –v
6>>>  install oracle instant client 
 rpm –i oracle-instantclient19.6-basic-19.6.0.0.0-1.x86_64.rpm
7>>>cd /<anyname>
8>>> unzip <file name>
9>>> cd <filename>
10>>> check the pm2 command is working or not.
	If command works then you will get output like below image.
 

	If command is not working than,
Run the command 
	npm install pm2 -g
After installation of pm2 , run the startup script by using below command.
	Pm2 start index.js

Check on the browser :-
https://<publicip>:7001
 
Rest API
1>>> pull the Nodejs RESTAPI Image from oracle registry
a.	Command to pull the application RestApi image 
b.	docker pull us-ashburn-1.ocir.io/orasenatdpltsecitom03/converged_db/convergedbapi:latest 
c.	check the docker image 
		docker images
d.	Run the docker image by using below command 
		docker run -it -d --restart always --name <container name (anything )> -p 3001:3001  <image Repo name>
e.	Execute the container 
docker exec -it <ContainerID> /bin/bash -c "cd /ConvergedbAPI/ConvergeDBAppAPI/ && pm2 start index.js --name ApplicationApi"


http://<Public IP>:3001/products     (To get all the product details)
http://<Public IP>:3001/products/<PID>    (To get the particular product details)
http://<Public IP>:3001/orderstatus   (to get the Order details) 


